Key Match Events: Donyell Malen scored an own goal in the 6th minute
Cody Gakpo equalized in the 47th minute
Romano Schmid scored for Austria in the 59th minute
Memphis Depay equalized for the Netherlands in the 75th minute
Marcel Sabitzer scored the winning goal for Austria in the 80th minute
Post-Match Reflections: Marcel Sabitzer: "When you win like that, win the group, score the winning goal, it doesn't get any better than that. You can see that we rotate through the team and nothing is missed, everyone knows their position and what they have to do"
Dutch captain Virgil van Dijk: "A very bad match, in all respects. We started weakly in possession and in duels. Then you are behind the times. It was a bad evening."
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria sped into a shock lead at the Olympiastadion
Austria's aggressive and hard-running approach propelled them into the round of 16
Austria topped the table with six points, one ahead of second-placed France on five and the Dutch on four points
Others: The Dutch also advanced as one of the four best third-place finishers
The final placings of the group were up in the air as positions in the standings changed several times over the 90 minutes
The game was played at the Olympiastadion Berlin
The game was covered by FS1
The line for the game was NED -0.5
The over/under for the game was 2.5
The referee for the game was Ivan Kruzliak from Slovakia
